---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"completions\", \"--help\"])"
---
Generate shell completions

Prints a completion script for the given shell to stdout; redirect it into the location your shell loads completions from.

Usage: hpds completions [OPTIONS] <SHELL>

Arguments:
  <SHELL>
          Shell to generate completions for
          
          [possible values: bash, elvish, fish, powershell, zsh]

Options:
  -v, --verbose
          Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress all output except errors

      --no-color
          Disable colored output

      --config <PATH>
          Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
